<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="CH1a0930-en-789ddc31" type="transl"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>PhD</title><editor role="translator">Tsao Ding-ren</editor></titleStmt><publicationStmt><ab>published electronically as part of the TLS project at https://hxwd.org</ab><availability status="4">The copyright status of this work is unclear</availability></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><bibl><title>PhD</title>University Michigan International, 1985</bibl><ab>Translation of <bibl corresp="#CH1a0930"><title xml:lang="och">鬼谷子</title></bibl> into <lang xml:lang="en">English</lang>.</ab></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><creation resp="#Isabelle">Initially created: <date>2024-07-29T21:38:42.186+09:00</date> by Isabelle</creation></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div><head>Translated parts</head><p xml:id="CH1a0930-start"><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:42:44.359+09:00">If we examine the past, </seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:43:18.571+09:00">we find that sages who have lived between heaven and earth</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:43:52.458+09:00">have always been ahead of ordinary beings.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:45:13.824+09:00">They observed the stirring and ceasing of yin and yang and named things according to their natures.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:45:52.475+09:00">They know the passages to survival or perdition.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:46:45.924+09:00">They can calculate the initiation and termination of all events.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:47:10.295+09:00">They understand the principles of the human mind.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:48:16.649+09:00">They are perceptive of the slightest signals of change</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:48:47.066+09:00">and can guard the passages (to survival or perdition). </seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:51:48.42+09:00">Therefore, from antiquity till now, </seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:51:42.678+09:00">the Way of all sages under heaven</seg><seg corresp="#CH1a0930_CHANT_001-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Isabelle" modified="2024-07-29T21:51:18.215+09:00">has been the same. </seg></p></div></body></text></TEI>